HORIZONWORKS NEW HIRE IT SETUP CHECKLIST
=========================================
Version 3.0 - Effective: January 2026
IT Operations Team

Welcome to HorizonWorks! This checklist will guide you through your 
technology setup. Most items should be completed on Day 1.

========================================================================
PRE-ARRIVAL (REMOTE EMPLOYEES)
========================================================================

Your laptop will be shipped to arrive 1-2 days before your start date.

[ ] Confirm shipping address with HR
[ ] Watch for FedEx tracking email from IT
[ ] DO NOT open the sealed laptop bag until Day 1 (security requirement)

========================================================================
DAY 1 SETUP - ALLOW 90 MINUTES
========================================================================

STEP 1: UNBOX AND POWER ON (10 min)
----------------------------------
[ ] Open laptop bag and remove all contents
[ ] Verify serial number matches your welcome email
[ ] Connect to power and turn on
[ ] Complete initial OS setup using temporary credentials from email

STEP 2: CLOUDFLARE ZERO TRUST SETUP (15 min)
-------------------------------------------
[IMPORTANT: This replaces the old Cisco VPN]

[ ] Open browser and navigate to: access.horizonworks.com
[ ] Sign in with your @horizonworks.com email
[ ] You'll be redirected to Okta - sign in with temporary password
[ ] Create new password (min 16 characters, no reuse of last 10)
[ ] Set up MFA using Okta Verify app on your phone:
    - Download "Okta Verify" from App Store / Google Play
    - Scan QR code shown on screen
    - Complete test verification
[ ] Install WARP client when prompted
[ ] Verify "WARP" icon shows connected (orange cloud icon)

STEP 3: CORE APPLICATIONS (20 min)
---------------------------------
Launch each app and sign in with your Okta credentials:

[ ] Chrome - Set as default browser
[ ] Slack - Join #general and #your-department
[ ] Google Workspace (Gmail, Calendar, Drive)
[ ] Notion - Our internal wiki and documentation
[ ] Zoom - Test audio/video
[ ] 1Password - Set up personal vault
    - IMPORTANT: Save your recovery kit in a safe place!

STEP 4: DEPARTMENT-SPECIFIC TOOLS (30 min)
-----------------------------------------
Engineering:
[ ] GitHub - Request access via #eng-access Slack channel
[ ] VS Code or JetBrains IDE
[ ] Docker Desktop
[ ] AWS SSO access (request via IT ticket if needed)

Sales/CS:
[ ] Salesforce
[ ] Gong
[ ] Zendesk

Marketing:
[ ] HubSpot
[ ] Figma (view access)
[ ] Canva

Product:
[ ] Figma
[ ] ProductBoard
[ ] Amplitude

Finance/HR:
[ ] Workday
[ ] Expensify
[ ] NetSuite (if applicable)

STEP 5: SECURITY COMPLIANCE (15 min)
-----------------------------------
[ ] Verify FileVault (Mac) or BitLocker (Windows) is enabled
    - Mac: System Settings > Privacy & Security > FileVault
    - Windows: Settings > Update & Security > Device Encryption
[ ] Install CrowdStrike Falcon (should auto-install)
    - Verify falcon icon in menu bar/system tray
[ ] Confirm automatic updates are enabled

