IMPORTANT POLICIES
========================================================================

EQUIPMENT:
- You may use your laptop for incidental personal use
- Do not install unauthorized software
- Report loss/theft IMMEDIATELY to IT (security risk)
- Equipment must be returned on your last day

REMOTE WORK:
- WARP must be connected when accessing company resources
- Use private WiFi only (no coffee shop networks for sensitive work)
- Enable screen lock when stepping away

DATA:
- Do not store company data on personal devices or cloud storage
- Use 1Password for all work credentials (no Chrome password saving)
- Report any suspected data exposure immediately

========================================================================
QUICK TROUBLESHOOTING
========================================================================

"WARP won't connect"
→ Click WARP icon > Preferences > Reset connection
→ If persists, sign out of Okta in browser and sign back in

"Can't access a website"
→ Verify WARP is connected
→ Try incognito window
→ Check #it-help for known outages

"MFA not working"
→ Ensure phone time is set to automatic
→ Use backup codes if needed (stored in 1Password)
→ Contact IT for MFA reset if locked out

"Need software not listed"
→ Submit request at support.horizonworks.com/software
→ All software must be approved for security compliance

